deleteNetGroup(25.10)                                    deleteNetGroup(25.10)

Name
       deleteNetGroup - Removes a net group that was created earlier

Syntax
       deleteNetGroup

       [-help]

       <netGroupName>

       Removes a net group that was created earlier.

       Note:  When  you  delete a net group, any bus guide associated with the
       net group also gets deleted.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each deleteNetGroup parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deleteNetGroup

       <netGroupName>
              Specifies  the name of the net group. You can use wildcards (*?)
              with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The following command removes netgroup NG_22.

       deleteNetGroup NG_22

